9 An Act relating to higher education; requiring the
Oklahoma State Regents for Higher Education conduct
10 feasibility study for implementing three-year
bachelor's degree programs; requiring study
11 investigate and analyze certain issues; requiring
State Regents to submit study report; providing for
12 codification; and declaring an emergency.
13
14
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
16 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
17 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 3252 of Title 70, unless there
18 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
19 A. The Oklahoma State Regents for Higher Education shall
20 conduct a thorough study to determine the feasibility of
21 implementing bachelor's degree programs that require only three (3)
22 years, or ninety (90) credit hours, to complete in this state. The
23 study shall investigate a variety of fields of study and determine
24 the feasibility of reducing specific course requirements, quantity
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB3315 SFLR Page 1
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 of e lectives, and total credit hours required for graduation. The
2 study shall consider and evaluate potential issues related to
3 accreditation and degree marketability.
4 B. On or before July 1, 2026, the State Regents shall prepare
5 and submit to the Governor, the Speaker of the Oklahoma House of
6 Representatives, and the President Pro Tempore of the Oklahoma State
7 Senate a report concerning the findings of the study.
8 SECTION 2. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
9 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
10 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
11 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
12 COMMITTEE REPORT BY: COMMITTEE ON EDUCATION
